 popular variation of satay (grilled skewers) common in Southeast Asian cuisine, especially in places like Singapore and Thailand. It is typically seasoned, skewered, grilled, and served with a peanut dipping sauce and condiments like cucumber and onion.','menu_items/rp19.png',0,0,'2025-11-30 10:55:21.453249','2025-12-03 06:10:12.448396',10,0),(198,'Sotong Satay per stick',6.50,'A large cuttlefish replaces the meat in normal satay. Is skewered and grilled over charcoal and severed ith peanut sauce, cucumber & onions.','menu_items/rp20.png',0,0,'2025-11-30 10:55:21.456313','2025-12-03 06:12:11.999071',10,0),(199,'Oyster Sauce with Vegetables',6.00,'A classic and simple side dish to pair with chicken rice is Chinese greens (like bok choy or gai lan) blanched or stir-fried and drizzled with a savory oyster sauce.','menu_items/rp56.png',0,0,'2025-11-30 10:56:40.455419','2025-12-05 10:06:30.704471',15,0),(200,'Beansprouts',6.00,'Ipoh Hainanese Chicken Rice is famous for its plump, crunchy, and slightly sweet bean sprouts, served as a side dish with their chicken rice.','menu_items/rp53.png',0,0,'2025-11-30 10:56:40.456947','2025-12-05 09:59:33.328620',15,0),(201,'Sambal Stingray',12.00,'Guan Kee stingray is a well-known BBQ sambal stingray from Singapore, famous for its fresh, tender fish and spicy-sweet sambal sauce. It is typically served on a banana leaf with a slice of lime for squeezing over the dish to enhance the flavor. The dish is praised for having a smoky flavor from the BBQ, a spicy kick from the chili, and a subtle sweetness, with the sambal clinging perfectly to the moist, flaky fish.','menu_items/gk1.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:07:29.068649','2025-12-01 14:26:01.651248',34,0),(202,'Lala',12.00,'Guan Kee\'s lala (clams) are known for being fresh and plump and is one of their highly rated dishes.','menu_items/gk2.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:07:29.072272','2025-12-01 14:22:09.082577',34,0),(203,'Curry Fish Head',25.00,'Guan Kee\'s Curry Fish Head is known for a fresh, tender red snapper fish head stewed in a thick, tangy, and aromatic curry gravy with a balanced mix of spices. It is served piping hot in a claypot with vegetables like eggplant, okra, long beans, cabbage, and tau pok. The dish is praised for its savory, spicy-tangy flavor profile, which pairs well with rice or fried bee hoon.','menu_items/gk4.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:12:36.880521','2025-12-01 14:18:26.851340',34,0),(204,'Chilli Crab',NULL,'Guan Kee Chilli Crab is a classic example of the iconic Singaporean dish served by Guan Kee Seafood, a local \"zi char\" (cookhouse) stall. The dish features fresh, meaty mud crab coated in a thick, rich sauce that is a harmonious blend of sweet, spicy, and savory flavors, typically served with deep-fried mantou buns for dipping','menu_items/gk3.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:12:36.881510','2025-12-01 14:16:25.585186',34,1),(205,'Deep Fried Baby Squid',15.00,'Guan Kee Seafood (Stall 53) at Newton Food Centre is known for its Crispy Baby Squid, which is a popular signature dish.','menu_items/gk5.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:12:36.882510','2025-12-01 14:20:27.298950',34,0),(206,'Gong Gong',12.00,'Gong Gong (Sea Snails): This seafood is known by the Malay name \"gonggong\". They have smooth, shimmering shells and are prized for their fresh, succulent, and tender meat. To eat them, the diner usually uses a small fork or toothpick to extract the snail from its shell.','menu_items/gk6.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:12:36.882510','2025-12-01 14:25:22.369320',34,0),(207,'Fried Hokkien Prawn Noodle',6.00,'Newton Old Signboard 25 Fried Hokkien Mee serves a well-balanced, \"wet-style\" plate of noodles highly regarded for its distinct wok hei (smoky aroma) and savory, umami-rich prawn broth. The dish achieves a balance of moisture that is neither too soupy nor too dry.','menu_items/rp34.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:58:20.917950','2025-12-05 07:59:46.298548',35,0),(208,'Fried Hokkien Lala Noodle',8.00,'The Fried Hokkien Lala Noodle from Newton Old Signboard 25 is their signature Hokkien Mee dish with the addition of fresh lala clams, providing an extra burst of seafood flavor and a distinct textural element.','menu_items/rp35.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:58:20.922280','2025-12-05 08:00:52.872921',35,0),(209,'Fried Hokkien Oyster Noodle',8.00,'The Fried Hokkien Oyster Noodle at Newton Old Signboard 25 takes their classic, smoky Hokkien Mee and enhances it with generous servings of fresh, briny oysters. This variation intensifies the overall seafood experience of the dish.','menu_items/rp36.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 14:58:20.923291','2025-12-05 08:02:13.442191',35,0),(210,'Oyster Omelette',6.00,'Hup Kee\'s Oyster Omelette is famous for its signature crispy, charred edges with a slightly gooey, starchy interior, loaded with generous, plump, and juicy oysters that are fried separately to retain flavor, all served with a tangy, piquant chili sauce, creating a delicious balance of textures and tastes.','menu_items/rp61.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:00:41.788859','2025-12-05 10:22:26.843649',36,0),(211,'Carrot Cake (Black)',4.00,'Heng Carrot Cake at Newton Food Centre is a Michelin Bib Gourmand-awarded stall famous for making its own radish cake in-house. The \"black\" version of the carrot cake is a popular choice, known for its distinct sweet and savory flavor profile and prominent wok hei (smoky aroma).','menu_items/rp38.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:41:55.232031','2025-12-05 08:06:31.549194',37,0),(212,'Carrot Cake (White)',4.00,'Heng Carrot Cake\'s \"white\" version (known locally as Chai Tow Kway) is highly regarded for its fluffy texture, golden-brown crispy edges, and savory flavor profile. Unlike the black version which uses sweet dark soy sauce, the white version highlights the natural flavors of the radish cake itself.','menu_items/rp39.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:41:55.242045','2025-12-05 08:08:54.536480',37,0),(213,'Oyster Omelette',8.00,'Heng Carrot Cake\'s Oyster Omelette (known locally as Orh Luak or Orh Jian) is a popular dish at Newton Food Centre, known for its superb execution and fresh ingredients. The stall has earned a Michelin Bib Gourmand award, partly due to the quality of this dish.','menu_items/rp41.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:41:55.247604','2025-12-05 08:12:34.738075',37,0),(214,'Braised Duck Rice',6.00,'Kwee Heng offers a Braised Duck Rice set that provides a complete meal featuring their signature boneless duck meat accompanied by several traditional Teochew side dishes. The set offers a variety of textures and flavors in one plate.','menu_items/rp45.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:44:28.423586','2025-12-05 08:26:07.424596',38,0),(215,'Braised Duck Noodles',5.00,'Kwee Heng\'s Braised Duck Noodles offer a flavorful alternative to their signature duck rice, providing a different texture and mouthfeel while using the same high-quality ingredients and traditional Teochew-style preparation.','menu_items/rp43.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:44:28.429120','2025-12-05 08:21:23.409050',38,0),(216,'Braised Duck Porridge',5.00,'The Braised Duck Porridge from Kwee Heng at Newton Food Centre is a comforting, traditional Teochew-style dish that provides a lighter alternative to the rice or noodle options, while still featuring their signature braised duck.','menu_items/rp44.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:44:28.432120','2025-12-05 08:24:01.620721',38,0),(217,'Boneless Duck Rice',4.00,'The Boneless Duck Rice is centered around thickly sliced, deboned duck meat that is exceptionally tender and succulent. The duck has been slow-braised in a savory, dark gravy with a subtle, balanced herbal essence, avoiding the overly medicinal taste sometimes found in other stalls.','menu_items/rp42.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:44:28.436648','2025-12-05 08:19:52.299778',38,0),(218,'Hainanese Chicken Rice',4.00,'Kwee Heng\'s Hainanese Chicken Rice is a staple offering alongside its signature duck dishes, providing a classic and comforting version of Singapore\'s unofficial national dish. The dish focuses on simple, well-executed flavors and quality ingredients.','menu_items/rp47.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:44:28.439648','2025-12-05 08:30:11.402689',38,0),(219,'Char Siew Roasted Pork Rice',4.00,'The dish combines two types of classic Cantonese-style roasted meats served over rice. Char Siew (BBQ Pork): The char siew is known for being tender and having a beautiful caramelized glaze. It typically features a good balance of lean meat and fat, sometimes with slightly charred edges, providing a mix of savory and sweet flavors.  Roasted Pork (Siew Yoke): The roasted pork is characterized by its crispy, crackling skin and moist, tender meat with balanced layers of fat. The skin provides an audible crunch (\"cruck cruck\") that is highly satisfying.','menu_items/rp46.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:44:28.444174','2025-12-05 08:28:27.331171',38,0),(220,'BBQ Chicken Wing',1.40,'R&B Express chicken wings are charcoal-grilled, crispy on the outside, juicy on the inside, and moderately flavorful, with a spicy sauce option. They are noted for being evenly grilled to a golden-brown color and often served with a tangy chilli sauce that complements the meat.','menu_items/rp8.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:48:54.955755','2025-12-02 13:41:57.766144',39,0),(221,'Beef Satay (per stick)',0.70,'R&B Express beef satay is a dish of marinated, skewered beef grilled on a charcoal grill and served with a peanut sauce. It features cubes of beef, typically cooked until slightly charred, and is a popular street food, especially in places like Singapore, often served as an appetizer or a main course.','menu_items/rp9.png',0,0,'2025-12-01 15:48:54.960831','2025-12-02 13:44:14.798351',39,0),(222,'Chicken Satay (per stick)',0.70,'R&B Express beef satay is a dish of marinated, skewered chicken grilled on a charcoal grill and served with a peanut sauce. It features cubes of beef, typically cooked until slightly charred, and is a popular street food, especially in places like Singapore, often served as an appetizer or a main course.','menu_items/rp10.png',0,0,'2025-12-02 13:39:58.487528','2025-12-02 13:45:28.389809',39,0),(223,'Pork Satay (per stick)',0.70,'Pork satay is a Chinese variation of the satay. Cubed pork is skewered on a stick and grilled over a charcoal fire, which imparts a distinct, smoky flavor.','menu_items/rp11.png',0,0,'2025-12-02 13:39:58.491565','2025-12-02 13:49:22.116733',39,0),(224,'Pohpiah',2.00,'R&B Express\'s popiah is a savory, soft-rolled snack with a filling of various ingredients including turnip, peanuts, egg, and vegetables, topped with sweet chili sauce.','menu_items/rp12.png',0,0,'2025-12-02 13:39:58.495090','2025-12-02 13:51:12.258025',39,0),(225,'Kueh Pie Tee',4.00,'R&B Express\'s \"Kueh Pie Tee\" is a Peranakan snack featuring a crispy, fried pastry shell filled with a savory mixture of shredded jicama (or yambean) and other vegetables, often garnished with sweet chili sauce or other condiments. Also known as \"top hats,\" this delicate, one-bite appetizer is a popular and beloved dish in Singapore and Malaysia.','menu_items/rp13.png',0,0,'2025-12-02 13:39:58.496100','2025-12-02 13:53:07.541622',39,0),(226,'Oyster Omelette (Add Oyster)',12.00,'Hup Kee\'s Oyster Omelette (Orh Luak) with added oysters is famous for its crispy, golden-brown exterior with soft, eggy interiors, packed with plump, fresh, juicy oysters, often fried separately for flavor, and served with a distinctive tangy, piquant chili sauce, offering a delicious contrast of textures and savory-sweet-spicy notes.','menu_items/rp61_yiUOuxS.png',0,0,'2025-12-02 13:58:07.310385','2025-12-05 10:24:42.775239',36,0),(227,'Oyster Egg (No Flour)',10.00,'Hup Kee\'s \"no flour\" oyster omelette (Orh Luak) is known for its eggy, crispy-edged, fluffy texture with fresh, plump oysters, offering a less gooey, more savory experience compared to the starchy versions, highlighted by its distinct Teochew flavor, aromatic depth, and tangy chili sauce that balances the rich, eggy taste without being overly oily.','menu_items/rp61_ylctfTU.png',0,0,'2025-12-02 13:58:07.311458','2025-12-05 10:23:40.862452',36,0),(228,'Oyster Eggs',6.00,'Heng Carrot Cake at Newton Food Centre (#01-28) also offers a very popular Oyster Omelette (known locally as Orh Luak or Orh Jian), which has earned its own fan base and contributes to the stall\'s Michelin Bib Gourmand status.','menu_items/rp40.png',0,0,'2025-12-02 14:01:43.927307','2025-12-05 08:11:05.099515',37,0),(229,'Fried Kway Tiao',6.00,'The Fried Kway Teow at Newton Old Signboard 25 is a popular dish known for its strong wok hei (smoky fragrance) and savory, slightly dark appearance. It is one of the stall\'s two main offerings, alongside their signature Hokkien Mee.','menu_items/rp37.png',0,0,'2025-12-05 07:57:04.078499','2025-12-05 08:02:57.637227',35,0);
