INSERT INTO `tours_tour` VALUES (1,'Street Art & Street Food Tour','walking','In this trail, we will discover the diversity of food of the main ethnic groups in Singapore. And while any foodie tour can take you on a hawker trail, we’ll let you in on the secrets behind the best stalls. \r\n\r\nThe private group is intentionally kept intimate as our food stops are small businesses specially handpicked to reflect artisanal techniques – not the ones typically visited by commercial tours. \r\n\r\nMore than tasting, you will also get a full palate education on the herbs & spices that are used in the traditional culinary kitchens of this region. In between eating stops, we take a breath to explore some terrific street art and walk through atmospheric alleys. This is the ultimate feast for the stomach and eyes!',210,10,599.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 10:02:07.523427','2025-12-02 13:28:06.328971',1,'tour_pics/rp5.png'),(2,'Feasting (off the Grid) at the Old Port','walking','Explore a lesser-known Singapore neighbourhood, featuring heritage shops, markets, street food and village-style dining experiences.\r\nHungry for an alternative Singapore? Join this food tour to spend 1/2 a day eating your way through a lesser-explored neighbourhood. We’ll dig into old-school shops, markets, UNESCO listed street food culture, and inside kampung (village)-style restaurants.',210,10,599.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 10:07:51.051505','2025-12-01 13:28:17.236615',1,'tour_pics/sm.png'),(3,'Signature Chinatown Walk – Free Walking Tour','walking','The one that started it all! Our first and signature tour. Join us for a 3 Hour Walk through the heart of Singapore.\r\n\r\nYou’ll be introduced to the City in a Garden and sneak a peek at how the locals live, play and eat.\r\n\r\nWe will bring you into Chinatown – a tourist attraction, but at the same time, also a local living area. Over the period of the tour, we hope that you will see how our unique blend of culture/religion/perspective has shaped Singapore to the city that it is today.\r\n\r\nThe walking tour aims to go deeper than just introducing the sites: we’ll stray off the beaten path and delve into the city’s amazing history. While we are at it, we will also show you some of our favorite eating spots!\r\n\r\nOf course, we’ll also try to provide you with an insider’s take on what you can do during your stay in Singapore.',180,25,0.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 10:38:21.294585','2025-12-05 10:48:56.789002',2,'tour_pics/rp4.png'),(4,'Hush: Night Food Tour through Geylang','walking','Geylang is one of our most unusual districts, and it truly comes alive at night with some of the tastiest supper places in Singapore.\r\n\r\nJoin us on a tantalizing food tour through the vibrant and colorful red light district. Discover the hidden culinary gems of this misunderstood neighborhood, as we venture into the bustling beer gardens and hole-in-the-wall food stalls. Savour the mouth-watering delights of traditional Singaporean cuisine, and wash it all down with a refreshing local beer (or fresh coconut juice).\r\n\r\nBut that’s not all, dear foodies – this tour also uncovers the secrets and stories of Geylang’s intriguing history and culture. Don’t miss out on this one-of-a-kind experience. Book your spot now and let’s embark on this tasty adventure together.',180,12,95.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 10:40:03.946714','2025-12-05 11:43:56.709492',2,'tour_pics/gy.png'),(5,'Market To Table Culinary Experience','cooking','Explore one of Singapore’s wet markets and learn how to bargain and buy ingredients like our locals do! After that, head back to the studio to whip up local favourites such as Chicken Rice, Hokkien Prawn Noodles, Kueh Dadar and more!',180,10,129.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 10:44:05.792847','2025-12-01 13:40:34.621979',3,'tour_pics/lgt2.png'),(6,'Let’s Go Cook – Discover Hokkien','cooking','The Hokkiens make up the largest Chinese dialect group in Singapore but what comes to mind when you think of Hokkien dishes? Not really sure? Come join us to learn more about Singapore’s local Hokkien culture and cuisine under the guidance of our local chef in this fun Singapore Cooking Class and Walking Tour!',180,10,129.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 10:45:28.794557','2025-12-01 13:37:31.121971',3,'tour_pics/lgt1.png'),(7,'Ang Mo Kio Neighbourhood Tour','vehicle','Our Ang Mo Kio Tour is one of our best selling tour that brings our guests to a local neighbourhood to see the places where local Singapore live, eat and play. Singaporeans originated from different countries and cultures, and this ‘rojak’ beginning is what gave us our unique identity today. This tour will take you beyond the city, to a place that can’t be found in travel guides and is unseen by tourists!\r\n\r\nIn this AMK tour, we start at the heartland location of Ang Mo Kio, where we will introduce you to a little know hobby that transcended the kampong era: birds singing. Brighten your morning with melodious chirps, and a visit to a ‘Kopitiam’ for coffee and toast like a true local. We will also visit a local wet market and a hawker centre.',120,10,65.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 10:56:13.080935','2025-12-01 13:26:21.605802',4,'tour_pics/ott1.png'),(8,'Private Michelin Premium Food Tour (Chinatown)','market','For the food lover, Singapore is a gastronomic paradise. Singapore may be a small dot on the map, but it has many more culinary delights to offer than many other countries that are much bigger.\r\n\r\nIf you’re a food lover, there are so many more food places for you to explore in Singapore. Join us on this mouth-watering Private Michelin Premium Food Tour adventure. Our team of food lovers has specially selected the restaurants and the food that we will be presenting to you. Our Singapore food tour includes two different Michelin Rated Restaurants and two other equally famous food/dessert stalls!\r\n\r\nIn this Singapore food tour, we do not only bring you good food, but we also bring you the BEST food!\r\n\r\nOur English speaking guides, who are also food lovers, will be conducting this guide.',210,10,105.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 11:00:48.638729','2025-12-05 11:04:00.904766',4,'tour_pics/rp3.png'),(9,'Toa Payoh Neighbourhood Tour (Heartland Tour)','market','Want to know how Singaporeans live?\r\n\r\nToa Payoh is the place to start. From squatters’ land to Singapore’s heartland—it was once an extensive and notorious squatter district, with many of its inhabitants engaging in farming and pig-rearing. Today, this housing estate is self-sufficient and has a town centre buzzing with shopping and entertainment. During its transformation, industrial developments were all within the town to provide residents with jobs close to their homes, and schools were built around the neighbourhood.\r\n\r\nIn this authentic Singapore tour, we’ll also bring you to visit Singapore’s iconic HDB Flat - more than 80% of Singaporeans live in one - and design your very own.',120,10,65.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 11:02:13.207373','2025-12-05 10:38:12.866360',4,'tour_pics/rp6.png'),(10,'Pulau Ubin Island Boat Tour + Kelong Visit','vehicle','Escape the concrete jungle, it’s time for an adventure! Cruise out to sea on our fine catamaran and discover the Northeastern waters of Singapore on this 3 hour Singapore Kelong Boat Tour.\r\n\r\nThe waters around the Northeastern islands are buzzing with a different kind of charm – seamen fishing, an abundance of nature, mangrove swamps and the idyllic life of residents who live in Kelongs (floating fish farms). All these are sights that normal city dwellers do not get to experience. We will also take you up-close to Pulau Ubin (the only inhabited island out of Singapore’s 63 islands) and explore it from the sea. Along the way, discover how Sustainable Fish Farming works in Singapore and learn about its struggles. Topping off the intriguing boat tour would be a visit to a kelong restaurant, where you get to experience life on a floating fish farm.\r\n\r\nSoak in the sun, let your hair down in the wind and just breathe in the salty sea air. It will be an unforgettable Singapore Boat Tour experience!',210,10,135.00,1,0,'2025-11-25 11:04:42.269525','2025-12-01 13:42:14.214315',3,'tour_pics/lgt3.png');
